  "text": "We have performed a weakly nonlinear analysis of cases when A = 0 and found, in agreement with [CITATION_1] that the chimney is born near the top of the mush. This is because the greatest upflow is predicted near the top of the mush when the rigid-lid assumption is abandoned. The analysis of hexagonal patterns predicts the boundary in parameter space at which up-and down-hexagons swap stability.",
  "correct_citation": {
